a:2:{s:6:"item-0";a:4:{s:15:"presenter_photo";s:4:"3136";s:14:"presenter_name";s:19:"Tracy Petrillo, EdD";s:21:"presenter_description";s:34:" CAE Chief Learning Officer, CASBO";s:13:"presenter_bio";s:964:"<p>Tracy Petrillo EdD, CAE is a thought leader in continuing professional education, adult learning, credentialing, certification, and leadership development. She is Chief Learning Officer for CASBO and recently completed her 3-year term on ASAE Honors &amp; Awards Committee. Dr. Petrillo’s accolades include: the national Association for Women Technology Champions (AWTC) 2023 Leadership Award, the 2016 ASAE Professional Performance Awardee, and being named a Changemaker by MeetingsNet magazine. She is past Chair of ASAE’s Certified Association Executive (CAE) Commission who speaks nationally on learning innovations and educational technologies to nonprofit, medical, corporate, and education audiences. She earned a doctorate in educational leadership and management with a specialization in human resource development. She is a pioneer in digital badging/credentialing and has conducted credential value research within professional associations.</p>
";}s:6:"item-1";a:4:{s:15:"presenter_photo";s:4:"3131";s:14:"presenter_name";s:12:"Amanda Davis";s:21:"presenter_description";s:45:"CMP Chief Experience Officer, Blue Sky eLearn";s:13:"presenter_bio";s:757:"<p>Amanda has over 15 years of experience in the association world, strategically focused on learning products. With multiple association roles as Director of Learning &amp; Development and Online Learning Manager, Amanda has a deep understanding of the adult learning landscape and what keeps association executives up at night. As Chief Experience Officer, Amanda now oversees the end-to-end experience for our growing mix of association clients. She is dedicated to fostering positive, productive relationships, and ensuring associations have an excellent experience partnering with our organization. Amanda draws on her background in learning strategy and association management to advise clients and shape an experience that enables their success.</p>
";}}

a:2:{s:6:"item-0";a:4:{s:15:"presenter_photo";s:4:"3144";s:14:"presenter_name";s:23:"Liam O'Malley, CAE, PMP";s:21:"presenter_description";s:56:"Vice President of Association Solutions, Blue Sky eLearn";s:13:"presenter_bio";s:694:"<p>Liam joined the Blue Sky eLearn team in 2019 as the Vice President of Association Solutions. With over 15 years of experience working with associations and non-profit organizations on a variety of technological projects, Liam brings a broad range of industry expertise and technical skill to the sales process. His in-depth knowledge of the association space allows him to communicate effectively to audiences no matter their background or experience level with technology. Additionally, Liam’s project management history brings an attention to detail in the process of evaluation and solution development, ensuring that all Blue Sky clients can begin their journey on the right foot.</p>
";}s:6:"item-1";a:4:{s:15:"presenter_photo";s:4:"3141";s:14:"presenter_name";s:8:"John Leh";s:21:"presenter_description";s:22:"CEO, Talented Learning";s:13:"presenter_bio";s:402:"<p>John Leh is the CEO, Lead Analyst and LMS selection consultant of Talented Learning. He’s a trusted learning tech industry veteran with over 25 years and $100 million-worth of front-line experience in buying and selling complex learning solutions. Since 2014, John has devoted himself to helping over 100 LMS buyers define their requirements and buy the right learning system for their needs.</p>
";}}

a:2:{s:6:"item-0";a:4:{s:15:"presenter_photo";s:4:"3148";s:14:"presenter_name";s:24:"Dr. Kristen Wall, MA EdD";s:21:"presenter_description";s:55:"Director of Learning &amp; Development, Blue Sky eLearn";s:13:"presenter_bio";s:1001:"<p>Dr. Kristen Wall, MA, EdD is the Director of Learning and Development at Blue Sky eLearn. Holding a master’s and doctorate in Adult Learning, Kristen specializes in bringing effective assessment strategies and qualitative research to enrich the learning programs of Blue Sky eLearn clients. Starting as a junior high teacher, Kristen’s journey led her to higher education, where she empowered countless online adult learners for over 15 years. Her passion for faculty development flourished, providing engaging learning opportunities for over 800 adjunct faculty members teaching 2,600 courses annually. In 2018, Kristen embraced a new adventure as a consultant, and destiny led her to Blue Sky eLearn, where she now thrives as the Director of Learning and Development. She’s worked with associations in a diverse group of industries, from medicine and healthcare to insurance and state government. Beyond her professional pursuits, she finds joy in hiking, travel, and detective novels.</p>
";}s:6:"item-1";a:4:{s:15:"presenter_photo";s:4:"3147";s:14:"presenter_name";s:19:"Jordan Baker, M.Ed.";s:21:"presenter_description";s:43:"Learning Solutions Advisor, Blue Sky eLearn";s:13:"presenter_bio";s:422:"<p>Jordan Baker is an innovative learning leader with over 15 years in literacy and adult education. As Learning Solutions Advisor for Blue Sky eLearn, she blends her educational expertise with strategic growth initiatives to empower clients in achieving their eLearning objectives. Holding an M.Ed. in Curriculum and Instruction, her contributions enrich professional development and lifelong learning opportunities.</p>
";}}

a:2:{s:6:"item-0";a:4:{s:15:"presenter_photo";s:4:"3153";s:14:"presenter_name";s:17:"Mark Wallach, MBA";s:21:"presenter_description";s:42:"CEO Emeritus, Mobile Engagement Strategies";s:13:"presenter_bio";s:1054:"<p>Mark Wallach, MBA, is the leading expert and advisor in the association community on innovative mobile technology, strategic planning, and collaborative partnerships. Mark empowers associations to implement powerful digital strategies that drive actual results. Serving as CEO Emeritus of Engagement Mobile Strategies, Mark’s distinguished insights have positioned him as a thought leader. He often contributes to ASAE: The Center for Association Leadership’s Associations Now and Association Chat magazine. He speaks at industry events, including ASAE’s Technology Conference &amp; Exposition, ASAE Idea Swap Series, The Association Podcast, Association Chat, and Professional Convention Management Association. Diagnosed with ALS in April 2021, Mark also speaks and advocates on behalf of the ALS Association and I Am ALS. Engagement Mobile Strategies is a consulting agency committed to helping associations increase member engagement, retention, and non-dues revenue through inclusive, accessible technology strategy and implementation.</p>
";}s:6:"item-1";a:4:{s:15:"presenter_photo";s:4:"1931";s:14:"presenter_name";s:12:"Jesse Shorts";s:21:"presenter_description";s:52:"Business Development Representative, Blue Sky eLearn";s:13:"presenter_bio";s:460:"<p>Jesse joined Blue Sky eLearn in February 2023. As our Business Development Representative, Jesse consistently enhances the knowledge and resources available to association professionals by forging strategic partnerships and introducing our innovative LMS and services. She came to us with experience in sales and the non-profit sector. When she’s not busy connecting with associations, she enjoys hiking, gardening, and whipping up new pasta recipes.</p>
";}}

a:3:{s:6:"item-0";a:1:{s:11:"description";s:123:"Understand the importance of digital accessibility in retaining and increasing the lifetime value of Baby Boomer members.
";}s:6:"item-1";a:1:{s:11:"description";s:99:"Explore strategies for implementing an accessible LMS to enhance member education and engagement.
";}s:6:"item-2";a:1:{s:11:"description";s:131:"Learn how to develop and promote legacy gifting programs that benefit both donors and the association's long-term financial health.";}}

a:2:{s:6:"item-0";a:4:{s:15:"presenter_photo";s:4:"3329";s:14:"presenter_name";s:12:"Dan Streeter";s:21:"presenter_description";s:38:"Chief Executive Officer, Mission Fuel ";s:13:"presenter_bio";s:334:"<p>Dan is an award-winning classroom teacher and school principal turned entrepreneur, now serving as the CEO and founder of Mission Fuel AI. Known for his passion for educational access for all Dan has built a career around helping associations and nonprofit organizations scale their impact through technology-powered learning.</p>
";}s:6:"item-1";a:4:{s:15:"presenter_photo";s:4:"3330";s:14:"presenter_name";s:12:"Jesse Shorts";s:21:"presenter_description";s:44:"Learning Programs Expert, Momentive Software";s:13:"presenter_bio";s:378:"<p>Jesse currently serves as our Channel Program Partner Manager. With over 2 years of experience in the association space, she is passionate about building strong relationships and supporting partners. Jesse plays a key role in driving program success by aligning partner goals with innovative LMS solutions, seamless onboarding, and collaborative go-to-market strategies.</p>
";}}

a:4:{s:6:"item-0";a:2:{s:13:"insight_title";s:24:"Membership Loyalty Surge";s:19:"insight_description";s:160:"Loyalty metrics improved across the board as members increasingly value collective benefits like representation, advocacy, and community during turbulent times.";}s:6:"item-1";a:2:{s:13:"insight_title";s:25:"Events as Revenue Drivers";s:19:"insight_description";s:176:"With events being the #2 revenue source after dues, associations are prioritizing successful events while adapting to budgetary and travel concerns through regional strategies.";}s:6:"item-2";a:2:{s:13:"insight_title";s:35:"Professional Development Evolution ";s:19:"insight_description";s:147:"A 7-point increase in required professional education creates opportunities for digital, on-demand learning beyond traditional conference models.
";}s:6:"item-3";a:2:{s:13:"insight_title";s:27:"AI Integration Acceleration";s:19:"insight_description";s:132:"AI usage jumped significantly with 40% of organizations now utilizing AI and having policies in place, supported by 61% of boards.
";}}

