a:2:{s:6:"item-0";a:4:{s:15:"presenter_photo";s:4:"4649";s:14:"presenter_name";s:14:"Chelsey Wilson";s:21:"presenter_description";s:48:"Sr Product Marketing Manager, Momentive Software";s:13:"presenter_bio";s:566:"<p>As a Senior Product Marketing Manager, Chelsey is passionate about understanding the evolving challenges and needs of modern nonprofit and association organizations. With a strong foundation in market research, industry analysis, and strategic positioning, Chelsey stays attuned to emerging trends that help organizations grow and adapt. Her diverse background in nonprofit leadership, marketing, and event management allows her to connect insights to practical applications—fueling her commitment to advancing the missions that strengthen our communities.</p>
";}s:6:"item-1";a:4:{s:15:"presenter_photo";s:4:"1690";s:14:"presenter_name";s:14:"Tirrah Switzer";s:21:"presenter_description";s:43:"VP of Product Marketing, Momentive Software";s:13:"presenter_bio";s:394:"<p>Tirrah is a product marketing enthusiast, borderline obsessed with keeping up to date with technology trends and understanding the challenges nonprofits and associations face. Tirrah is the VP of Product Marketing with Momentive Software. She is the co-author of 11 research studies on nonprofit and event trends, member engagement and loyalty, and association digital evolution trends.</p>
";}}

a:1:{s:6:"item-0";a:4:{s:15:"presenter_photo";s:4:"6530";s:14:"presenter_name";s:12:"Chris Barlow";s:21:"presenter_description";s:39:"Founder and Customer Happiness Director";s:13:"presenter_bio";s:528:"<p><img class="alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-6531" src="https://momentivesoftware.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/FullDesign-Color-Square-150x150.png" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></p>
<p>As Founder and Customer Happiness Director of Beeline, Chris Barlow is grateful to help nonprofits use digital marketing to multiply the reach of their mission and the growth of their donors. Most of all, he’s grateful to be the dad to eight kids, and to try to teach them how to live in a way that multiplies good in others.</p>
";}}

a:2:{s:6:"item-0";a:4:{s:15:"presenter_photo";s:4:"9754";s:14:"presenter_name";s:14:"Nikkii Kashub ";s:21:"presenter_description";s:50:"Director of Donor Management Solutions - GiveSmart";s:13:"presenter_bio";s:707:"<p>Nikkii Kashub is the current Director of Donor Management Solutions for GiveSmart and has served the nonprofit community for over 17 years. Her first taste of fundraising was in 2006 when she developed a philanthropic committee among friends to raise funds for Alex’s Lemonade Stand and the National Kidney Foundation. In 2010, Nikkii combined her love of philanthropy with her background in computer science to start a career in the donor management software industry helping nonprofit organizations save time while raising more money. Nikkii volunteers regularly for the local homeless shelter and spends time teaching small business marketing strategies to women entrepreneurs in her community.</p>
";}s:6:"item-1";a:4:{s:15:"presenter_photo";s:4:"9754";s:14:"presenter_name";s:15:"Ryan Woroniecki";s:21:"presenter_description";s:18:"Advisor - Momentum";s:13:"presenter_bio";s:580:"<p>Ryan has spent over a decade helping nonprofits. During his time at DonorSearch he helped thousands of nonprofits use fundraising insights from inside their CRM. He helped design and implement prospect management systems and processes at for-profit and nonprofit organizations. At Lighthouse Counsel he designed the firm’s first-ever AI-powered analytics solution. As Chair of The Giving USA Resource Development Committee, he closed some of the largest-ever gifts to the annual fund and helped achieve 100% Giving Institute member firm participation in the annual fund.</p>
";}}

a:2:{s:6:"item-0";a:4:{s:15:"presenter_photo";s:4:"9879";s:14:"presenter_name";s:30:"Celeste Flores - GivingTuesday";s:21:"presenter_description";s:25:"Director, US + Canada Hub";s:13:"presenter_bio";s:993:"<p>Celeste Flores directs GivingTuesday’s United States + Canada Hub. In that work, she supports and mobilizes a network of hundreds of local community leaders across the country to inspire local generosity. She works with leaders on growing their local giving movements, developing collaborations, and activating communities of diverse cultures, causes, and identities to include everyone in meaningful giving. Celeste is a strategist focused on social good and community-led efforts with decades of experience in creating vision with cross-sections of a community to building partnerships that will expand local impact, sustainability, and generosity. Celeste has also held leadership positions at I Live Here I Give Here in Austin, Texas, Foundation For the Carolinas in Charlotte, University of Virginia Darden School of Business, Texas Children’s Hospital and the United Way in Houston as well as Accenture. Celeste is based in the Washington DC area but is a big Texan at heart.</p>
";}s:6:"item-1";a:4:{s:15:"presenter_photo";s:4:"1007";s:14:"presenter_name";s:15:"Kathy Nothnagel";s:21:"presenter_description";s:47:"Manager, Content Marketing - Momentive Software";s:13:"presenter_bio";s:423:"<p>Kathy Nothnagel leads the content team at Momentive Software, supporting the thousands of nonprofits who power their communities with GiveSmart and MIP. With over 15 years as a professional and volunteer fundraiser, Kathy is passionate about helping mission-driven work and nonprofit staff. When she is away from her thesaurus, Kathy enjoys spending time with and exploring with her family in their home of Chicago.</p>
";}}

a:2:{s:6:"item-0";a:4:{s:15:"presenter_photo";s:4:"9889";s:14:"presenter_name";s:13:"Brandon Lyons";s:21:"presenter_description";s:43:"SVP of Strategic Partnerships - DonorSearch";s:13:"presenter_bio";s:375:"<p>Brandon Lyons has been with DonorSearch since 2015 and is currently the SVP of Strategic Partnerships. For the past 9 years, he has worked in the nonprofit sector. Brandon graduated from the University of Maryland with a degree in Micro-Biology and is also a small business owner. He speaks fluent German and in his spare time enjoys painting, drawing, and gardening.</p>
";}s:6:"item-1";a:4:{s:15:"presenter_photo";s:4:"9657";s:14:"presenter_name";s:15:"Madison Kautman";s:21:"presenter_description";s:35:"Senior Campaign Manager - GiveSmart";s:13:"presenter_bio";s:490:"<p>Madison Kautman is the Senior Campaign Manager for GiveSmart and a fundraising professional with a passion for the arts and culture sector. Before joining the GiveSmart team, Madison worked within many nonprofit organizations including art galleries, art museums, children’s museums, and a healthcare clinic. In addition, she was a GiveSmart customer for about two years, utilizing the platform to facilitate many events and fundraisers to make a difference in her community. ​</p>
";}}

a:2:{s:6:"item-0";a:4:{s:15:"presenter_photo";s:4:"9671";s:14:"presenter_name";s:12:"Elon Packin ";s:21:"presenter_description";s:20:"Head of Partnerships";s:13:"presenter_bio";s:319:"<figure class="wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><a href="https://www.givechariot.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external" data-wpel-link="external"><img class="wp-image-11608" src="https://www.givesmart.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Chariot-Logo.png" alt="" width="254" height="58" /></a></figure>
";}s:6:"item-1";a:4:{s:15:"presenter_photo";s:4:"9672";s:14:"presenter_name";s:14:"Pooya Pourak  ";s:21:"presenter_description";s:15:"Co-Founder, CEO";s:13:"presenter_bio";s:276:"<p><a href="https://www.matchnice.org/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener external" data-wpel-link="external"><img class="wp-image-11610" src="https://www.givesmart.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/MatchNice-Logo-1024x207.png" alt="" width="1024" height="207" /></a></p>
";}}

